      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.qIIoypmTFypnmRer]{Evolutionist Adaption}</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your more powerful transformations can knock back bystanders. As a reaction when you spend 2 or more MP to use an adaptation, you can push away one or more creatures adjacent to you, moving them 5 feet away as if you had succeeded at a @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.U37n5tY5hn1ctzQL.JournalEntryPage.R33uiOMesYP0ISWl#bull-rush]{bull rush} attempt against them (Fortitude negates). This movement doesn&rsquo;t provoke attacks of opportunity. When you activate this adaptation, if you&rsquo;ve spent 4 or more MP since the end of your last turn, you also make any pushed creature @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.MZ8OoH1GE9qDMyCD]{flat-footed} until the end of your next turn. Once you use this adaptation, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you have rested 10 minutes to regain Stamina Points. <br></span></p>"
